From todays Yahoo finance Simply Wall Street - PAR&#39;s 2024 numbers were adjusted down -  &#34;the consensus from eight analysts covering PAR Technology is for revenues of US$353m in 2024, implying a definite 17% decline in sales compared to the last 12 months. Losses are expected to increase slightly, to US$2.19 per share. Yet prior to the latest estimates, the analysts had been forecasting revenues of US$406m and losses of US$1.79 per share in 2024. So there&#39;s been quite a change-up of views after the recent consensus updates, with the analysts making a serious cut to their revenue forecasts while also expecting losses per share to increase.&#34;

However, are these analysts comparing apples to apples. Did the initial estimates include PAR Government and Rome Research revenue and profit? If so, they have been sold, TASK was just purchased and PAR is now a pure play. The focus should be on next year not 2024.

But, mgt does need to concentrate on true integration, elimination of silos and PROFITABILITY!
